'''''The New York Sun''''' was an American&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/3111116/Conservative-US-newspaper-New-York-Sun-closes.html|title=Conservative US newspaper New York Sun closes|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|location=London|date=September 30, 2008|first=Tom|last=Leonard|access-date=April 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171114170320/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/3111116/Conservative-US-newspaper-New-York-Sun-closes.html|archive-date=November 14, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/30/nyregion/30sun.html|title=Losing Money, New York Sun Is to Shut Down|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=September 29, 2008|first=James|last=Barron|access-date=February 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170311045518/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/30/nyregion/30sun.html|archive-date=March 11, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}&lt;/ref&gt; [[daily newspaper]] published in [[Manhattan]] from 2002 to 2008. It debuted on April 16, 2002, adopting the name, motto, and [[Nameplate (publishing)|masthead]] of the earlier New York paper, ''[[The Sun (New York City)|The Sun]]'' (1833–1950). It became the first general-interest [[broadsheet]] newspaper to be started in New York City in several decades. Its [[op-ed]] page became a prominent platform in the country for [[Conservatism in the United States|conservative]] viewpoints. Since 2009 ''The Sun'' has operated as an (occasional and erratic) online-only publisher of political and economic opinion pieces, as well as occasional arts content.

==History==
''The Sun'' was founded by a group of investors including publishing magnate [[Conrad Black]]. The goal was to provide an alternative to ''[[The New York Times]]'', featuring front page news about local and state events, in contrast to the emphasis on national and international news by the ''Times''. The Sun began business operations, prior to first publication, in October 2001.&lt;ref name=&quot;ap-end&quot;/&gt;
